Government officials have repeatedly insisted there is no evidence to support universal screening for Group B Strep, known as GBS .
But despite the fact it is carried by one in four women and infects as many as 400 newborns in the UK every year .
A programme which offered screening to all expectant women at Northwick Park NHS hospital in North-West London resulted in not a single case of the bacteria spreading to infants among those who had not agreed to be tested .